text: listen it's to me it comes to the
product and the brand and and frankly
the product and the brand that this
founding team Travis and his founding
team have built is extraordinary and the
talent of the company is extraordinary
and the culture went wrong and the
governance of the company went wrong and
the board went in a very bad direction
but if the product is good then if you
can bring in good leadership and you can
ultimately bring it together and I think
we're on our way we're on our way it's
gonna take a lot of work but after two
months I feel better about where we are
then frankly I was going in you can talk
about culture etc but the fact is that
everyone wants to plan a winning team
and I think that even if you have a
great culture and you're constantly
losing you're not really gonna love it
the magic is when you're playing on a
winning team and you have a great
culture and at the same time teams who
win sometimes the winning can hide rot
that can happen in an organization and I
think that uber was winning and while it
was scaling as a business it wasn't
necessarily scaling in terms of culture
and and scaling in terms of some of the
executives there and Travis try to bring
in some senior executives that just
didn't work out
and I think winning gave some excuses
for bad behavior
and it happened over a period of time
and by the time that it kind of became
public it was almost too late and the
thing that the company recognized and
Travis has recognized is that they need
it to change and they needed to change
fast which is why I think they
ultimately decided that they needed a
new executive in there
